      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Early 20th-century eugenicists argued that human evolution was a linear process where \"superior\" races, often defined by European phenotypes, were naturally destined to dominate, while \"inferior\" races were viewed as degenerate and incapable of improvement. They falsely claimed that intelligence and morality were directly tied to physical traits like skull shape and skin color, using pseudoscientific methods to assert that mixing these races would lead to the extinction of the \"superior\" group. This racist ideology was later weaponized to justify colonization, forced sterilization, and the systematic oppression of marginalized communities under the guise of \"improving\" the human gene pool.",
